HEADWORD: Streamy
<hw>Stream"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding
with streams, or with running water; streamful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Arcadia⟦br⟧
However <qex>streamy</qex> now, adust and dry,⟦br⟧
Denied the goddess water.</q> <rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling a stream; issuing in a stream.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His nodding helm emits a <qex>streamy</qex> ray.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stree</ent>⟦br⟧
